Bring a large pot of water to a boil. Cook asparagus for 1 minute. Drain. Rinse and cool under cold water. Pat asparagus dry with paper towels. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Toast pine nuts for 5-7 minutes. Cool. Arrange asparagus on a platter, top with peppers and parsley. Pour Marzetti Italian Blue Cheese Crumble Dressing over all. Sprinkle with toasted pine nuts. Serve.